{
  "texts": [
    "We argue that high-quality polling results should also count as essential knowledge.",
    "In electoral democracies, voters have a stake in a certain type of knowledge.",
    "They need access to suitable information about each candidate and their platform on the basis of which they can form their preferences and make the best available choice.",
    "Goldman usefully theorised the notion of 'core voter knowledge', conceived of as a democratic value which is essential to the well-functioning of an electoral democracy.",
    "Simply put, core voter knowledge is what allows voters to decide which candidate would be better by their own light."
  ]
}